String.fromCharCode();
  //DEFINITION
  //The static String.fromCharCode() method returns a string created by using the specified sequence of Unicode values.
  
  //SYNTAX
  //String.fromCharCode(num1[, ...[, numN]])
  
  //EXAMPLE
  //String.fromCharCode(65, 66, 67);  // "ABC"
  
  //USE CASE
  //I used this method in order to determine the char code location of a letter on a string
  //String.fromCharCode(str[i]);
  
.charCodeAt();
  //DEFINITION
  //The charCodeAt() method returns the numeric Unicode value of the character at the given index (except for unicode codepoints > 0x10000).

  //SYNTAX
  //str.charCodeAt(index)
  
  //EXAMPLE
  //'ABC'.charCodeAt(0); // returns 65 because A is char code 65
  
  //USE CASE
  //I called this method when I needed to get the first character of a string inside the String.fromCharCode() method
  //String.fromCharCode(str[i].charCodeAt(0));
  
  
